<h1><%= title %></h1>

<p>Interested in applying for a TGIF grant? Follow the steps below. There is also <a href=/img/tgif-funding-process.pdf>an infographic</a> you can follow.

<h2 class=counted>Am I eligible to apply?</h2>
<ul class=checklist>
	<li>I am a UCLA student, staff member, or faculty member (can be applying on behalf of an organization).
</ul>

<h2 class=counted>Does my project meet the requirements to apply to TGIF?</h2>
<ul class=checklist>
	<li>The project promotes environmental sustainability on UCLA's campus in accordance with <a href=/about/mission>our mission</a>.
	<li>The project has a clearly-defined, measurable outcome.
	<li>The project has a mechanism for evaluation and follow-up after funding has been disbursed.
	<li class=checklist-tip>Learn more about <a href=https://docs.google.com/document/d/12ljIO5E2N_gr86mvmcEyPQr9n2mkA_tgU3j8DktL7Fc/view>TGIF guidelines</a>.
</ul>

<h2 class=counted>The application process and expected timeline.</h2>
<ul class=checklist>
	<li class=checklist-tip>When creating your budget, reference this <a href=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Khwpb1E-wLjETS9UuADD3HXHHFyvROszF5jNtMjc1tM/view>sample budget</a>.</li>
	<li><a href=/apply/mini/>TGIF Mini Fund</a> (requesting $1,000 or less)
		<ul>
			<li>Fill out an application before the deadline.
			<li>Within two weeks of the funding deadline, you will receive your allocation via email.
			<li class=checklist-tip>Funding closes Friday of Week 8 each quarter. If you miss a deadline, your application will be considered in the next funding round. No funding is awarded during the summer.
		</ul>
	<li><a href=/apply/main/>TGIF Main Fund</a> (requesting $10,000 or less)
		<ul>
			<li>Fill out an application before the deadline.
			<li>Sign up for a hearing (the link will be sent a week following the deadline).
			<li>Attend the hearing.
			<li>Within two weeks of the hearing, you will receive your allocation via email.
			<li class=checklist-tip>Funding closes Friday of Week 2 each quarter. If you miss a deadline, your application will be considered in the next funding round. No funding is awarded during the summer.
		</ul>
	<li><a href=/apply/capital/>Capital/<wbr>Infrastructure Projects</a> (requesting more than $10,000)
		<ul>
			<li>Fill out an application (accepted on a rolling basis).
			<li>Within two weeks of the funding deadline, you will receive your allocation via email.
			<li>If funded, you will schedule quarterly meetings with the Grant Coordinator.
			<li class=checklist-tip>Funding closes Friday of Week 8 Spring Quarter. If you miss this deadline, you must wait until the next academic year. No funding is awarded during the summer.
		</ul>
</ul>

<h2 class=counted>Ready to access funding allocation?</h2>
Please follow <a href=/access>these instructions</a>.

<h2 class=counted>Don't forget your project summary report!</h2>
<ul class=checklist>
	<li>After you have spent your funds to complete your project, you must fill out our <a href=/projects/report>project summary report</a>.
	<li>This report helps provide feedback to TGIF and provides content for us to highlight previously funded projects on our website and social media.
</ul>
